Market multiple valuation of Companhia de Locacao das Americas ( LCAM3 | BRA)The most common multiple used in the valuation of stocks is the P/Earnings NTM multiple (Price to Earnings). P/E relates the current share price with the market expectations in terms of Earnings Per Share. This multiple is used to compare a company's market value with its earnings. A company with a high P/Earnings NTM is considered to be overvalued; a company with a low P/Earnings NTM is considered to be undervalued.The P/Earnings NTM ratio of Companhia de Locacao das Americas is slightly higher than the median of its peer group: around 11.00. The company valuation of Companhia de Locacao das Americas according to these metrics is consistent with the market valuation of its peer group.The P/Earnings NTM ratio of Companhia de Locacao das Americas is significantly lower than the average of its sector (Travel & Tourism): 19.00. The company valuation of Companhia de Locacao das Americas according to these metrics is way below the market valuation of its sector.The P/Earnings NTM ratio of Companhia de Locacao das Americas is significantly higher than its historical 5-year average: 8.9. The  (current) company valuation of Companhia de Locacao das Americas is therefore way above its valuation average over the last five years.Valuation



